g.text: In 1970, Japan is leading these five countries in trademark applications totalling 139, 414. Brazil with 32,344; The United States with 33,326; and India with 7,400. In 1980, China submits its first year of applications with 26,177.

In 1963, India enters with submitting 6,707 trademark applications. In 1970, Japan is leading the listed countries with 139,414, and U.S. is trailing far behind with only 33,326. * Chart is a placeholder. Text is accurate

In 1950, Japan is leading trademark applications with 29,841, double that of Brazil, which submitted 14,474. The United States is in second with 17,975. Ten years later in 1960, Brazil gains the lead with 42,444 applications.
